{"title":"Four new Bike Tools from Clever Standard, Equipt & Enduro","link":"https://bikerumor.com/new-bike-tools-from-clever-standard-equipt/","date":1710379852000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/clever-standard-sea-plastic-waste-tire-plugger-tool-800x527.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"527\" alt=\"clever standard bacon anchor net tubeless tire plug kit made from reclaimed plastic ocean waste\" /></p>\n<p>A couple of tools stood out at the 2024 Taipei Cycle Show, both with a seaworthy theme. Above, the new <a href=\"https://bibcreative.bigcartel.com/product/bacon-anchor-net\" target=\"_blank\">Bacon Anchor Net</a> bullet tips from Clever Design, which are made from reclaimed plastic ocean waste.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Originally (and still) offered in metal, these plastic tire plugger tips capture the plug strip and attach to any 2mm hex tool. Simply slide the plug through the tip, attach it to your existing mini-tool, and press it into your tire. The tip keeps the plug captured in the tire so it won’t get yanked out in a skid if you don’t have anything to cut it with.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The version shown above is a limited edition “model” kit with pop-out handle and plugger tip that threads into it. The handle doubles as a storage pod for plugs and bullet tips. Pop out all the pieces and assemble! The entire thing is made from plastic sea waste, too. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Equipt Sardine &amp; Cucumber bike tools</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-sardine-bicycle-multitool-1.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1500\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-sardine-bicycle-multitool-1.jpg\" alt=\"equipt sardine multi tool with flip-out bits and bike frame mount\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-sardine-bicycle-multitool-1.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-sardine-bicycle-multitool-1-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-sardine-bicycle-multitool-1-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-sardine-bicycle-multitool-1-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-sardine-bicycle-multitool-1-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-sardine-bicycle-multitool-1-1536x1152.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.alternative-bikes.com/item/item.php?page_no=&amp;goods_code=M057&amp;genre_code=&amp;brand_code=&amp;back_page=index.php\">Equipt Tool’s Sardine</a> is a compact, solidly-built mini tool featuring 3/4/5/6 hex bits and a Torx 25. The body is aluminum, with steel tool bits, and the whole thing weighs just 38g. The smaller bits all swivel 180º, making it easy to get hte angle you need when making a repair, then folding them flat for storage.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-sardine-bicycle-multitool-2.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1500\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-sardine-bicycle-multitool-2.jpg\" alt=\"equipt sardine multi tool with flip-out bits and bike frame mount\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-sardine-bicycle-multitool-2.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-sardine-bicycle-multitool-2-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-sardine-bicycle-multitool-2-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-sardine-bicycle-multitool-2-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-sardine-bicycle-multitool-2-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-sardine-bicycle-multitool-2-1536x1152.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The tool is made in Japan and retails for $60-70 USD (shop around). A bike frame holster sold separately and has two sets of holes to fit different widths of bike frames. Available in a variety of colors.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-cucumber-8mm-flip-flop-pedal-wrench-2.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1305\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-cucumber-8mm-flip-flop-pedal-wrench-2.jpg\" alt=\"equipt cucumber bicycle pedal tool with flip out 8mm hex bit\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-cucumber-8mm-flip-flop-pedal-wrench-2.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-cucumber-8mm-flip-flop-pedal-wrench-2-297x194.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-cucumber-8mm-flip-flop-pedal-wrench-2-800x522.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-cucumber-8mm-flip-flop-pedal-wrench-2-120x78.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-cucumber-8mm-flip-flop-pedal-wrench-2-768x501.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-cucumber-8mm-flip-flop-pedal-wrench-2-1536x1002.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Their upcoming Cucumber pedal wrench tool adds a longer lever with hole at the end to hang it in your workshop. The tool end has a swiveling 6mm and 8mm to fit most pedals.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-cucumber-8mm-flip-flop-pedal-wrench.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1312\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-cucumber-8mm-flip-flop-pedal-wrench.jpg\" alt=\"equipt cucumber bicycle pedal tool with flip out 8mm hex bit\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-cucumber-8mm-flip-flop-pedal-wrench.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-cucumber-8mm-flip-flop-pedal-wrench-297x195.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-cucumber-8mm-flip-flop-pedal-wrench-800x525.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-cucumber-8mm-flip-flop-pedal-wrench-120x79.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-cucumber-8mm-flip-flop-pedal-wrench-768x504.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/equipt-cucumber-8mm-flip-flop-pedal-wrench-1536x1008.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>MSRP and availability TBA. Follow them <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/equipt_japan\" target=\"_blank\">on Instagram</a> for updates.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Enduro Quick-Release Bearing Press Tool</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/enduro-bearings-quick-release-bearing-press-tool-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1350\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/enduro-bearings-quick-release-bearing-press-tool-2.jpg\" alt=\"enduro bearings quick release bearing press tool\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/enduro-bearings-quick-release-bearing-press-tool-2.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/enduro-bearings-quick-release-bearing-press-tool-2-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/enduro-bearings-quick-release-bearing-press-tool-2-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/enduro-bearings-quick-release-bearing-press-tool-2-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/enduro-bearings-quick-release-bearing-press-tool-2-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/enduro-bearings-quick-release-bearing-press-tool-2-1536x1152.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Enduro Bearing’s new quick-release version of their <a href=\"https://cycling.endurobearings.com/collections/tools\" target=\"_blank\">Linear Bearing Press Tool</a> uses a split threaded press tip that lets you quickly slide it close to the bearings, then snap the T-handle on to close it onto the threaded shaft.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Normally, you’d need to thread it all the way down the shaft, which can take some time to both install, and then also to remove the tool. Enduro’s Matt Harvey got tired of all that spinning, so he developed this version of a quick-release design.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/enduro-bearings-quick-release-bearing-press-tool-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2025\" height=\"750\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/enduro-bearings-quick-release-bearing-press-tool-1.jpg\" alt=\"enduro bearings quick release linear bearing press tool\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/enduro-bearings-quick-release-bearing-press-tool-1.jpg 2025w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/enduro-bearings-quick-release-bearing-press-tool-1-297x110.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/enduro-bearings-quick-release-bearing-press-tool-1-800x296.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/enduro-bearings-quick-release-bearing-press-tool-1-120x44.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/enduro-bearings-quick-release-bearing-press-tool-1-768x284.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/enduro-bearings-quick-release-bearing-press-tool-1-1536x569.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In typical Enduro fashion, it’s very well built. The threaded tips have threads on both sides, not just one, which is more common on less expensive tools. This gives it excellent bite and even pressing as you twist the handle. To release, just pull the handle back until it snaps off of the bit and slide everything off. Various bits are included in a complete kit, giving mechanics everything they’ll need for modern hubs, BBs, etc. Coming soon, price TBA.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/new-bike-tools-from-clever-standard-equipt/\">Four new Bike Tools from Clever Standard, Equipt &amp; Enduro</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"79e9c87de07c5183570797769655ad84ab3430f1f066a8b5c3b7d8a96488da21","category":"Cycling"}